Location: Petronas Towers, Kuala Lumpur Malaysia

The most iconic structure in Kuala Lumpur is without a doubt the Petronas Towers. No trip to Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia is complete without getting selfie in front of the tower! 

Unfortunately, it's quite expensive to visit the skybridge that connects the Petronas Towers. For this reason, we decided to enjoy the view of the towers from the ground.

You can go inside the bottom of the Petronas Towers for free. The small structure between the two towers is a giant shopping mall, complete with food court that offers all kinds of affordable meal options.

If you want to know what it's like to visit the Petronas Towers in Kuala Lumpur check out this VLOG!

title: INCREDIBLE Elephant Sanctuary Experience - Chiang Mai, Thailand 2016
description:
âœˆï¸  We created an app to help you save up to 80% on international flights! Try it risk free  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160310.1 â¬…ï¸

This adventure made possible by: http://www.elephantjunglesanctuary.com/

Visiting an Elephant Sanctuary in Chiang Mai, Thailand was an unforgettable experience! We booked our day at the Elephant Sanctuary through the Elephant Jungle Sanctuary!

We opted to spend a full day at the Elephant Jungle Sanctuary so that we could spend as much time as possible interacting with the Elephants! We would gladly recommend this tour to anyone visiting Chiang Mai.

When booking an elephant experience in Chiang Mai, Thailand, make sure to do your research about the elephants, and definitely donâ€™t book a tour that includes riding the elephants! In order for the elephants to be tamed enough for humans to ride them, they must be put through brutal torture as baby. This allows the owners of the elephants to break their spirits until they become totally submissive to humans.

Please donâ€™t support this type of business! Instead, support an elephant sanctuary or reserve such as the Elephant Jungle Sanctuary. The elephants are treated much better! Plus, it way more fun to feed and bathe the elephants that it is to ride them!

title: SHIPWRECKS & SHARKS! Diving in the Dominican Republic GRAND FINALE!
description:
Could our diving in the Dominican Republic have ended any better?! We feel like we have discovered a hidden gem in the Caribbean! We did the BEST dives of our whole trip on our last 2 days in La Romana. We dove the MASSIVE St. George shipwreck with the most fish we've ever seen, then saw 2 sharks with our new "Shark Whisperer" scuba guide ;) We ended the day on the most beautiful island of Saona and can't think of a better way to end of our time in the DR!

Travel vlog 577 | La Romana, Dominican Republic | Country #83/100

description:

Homemade pizza in a brick oven, vespa drives through the Italian countryside, visiting the smallest alley in Italy, getting lost in the cutest hill town ever, filling up a gallon jug of wine for 3 euros, and eating in front of the sunset with friends - These are all the reasons we had to create a MINI MOVIE :) 

Thank you Bob & Gina!!! :)

title: MIDDLE EAST CRUISE STOP #4: DOHA WITH LOCALS!
description:
100k GIVEAWAY! ENTER HERE: https://karaandnate.com/100k-giveaway/
HOW WE TRAVEL FOR â€œFREEâ€: http://learn.karaandnate.com/p/30-days-to-becoming-a-travel-hacker/
FREE GUIDE TO AIRPORT LOUNGE ACCESS:
http://karaandnate.com/the-ultimate-guide-to-lounge-access/ 

We are on a cruise with MSC (Splendida ship), and today was our 4th stop at our 70th country of Qatar! A very nice couple offered to pick us up and take us around Doha for the day :) Our first stop was the camel race track! Some locals were there training, then they invited us into their house for coffee and pool (WHAT?!). We got to hang out with them, their camels, AND their racing falcon! Next we went out for a authentic lunch at the Waqif Souq. We ended the day with a view of the Doha skyline lighting up at sunset from our ship! Thank you Kim and Nash for a wonderful day in Doha! :)

Today we had the opportunity to visit the Hobbiton New Zealand movie set. Kara and I are both BIG Lord of the Rings and Hobbit fans so when we started to plan our trip to New Zealand we knew we wanted to visit Hobbiton! While RVing around New Zealand we stopped close to the town of Cambridge, New Zealand where the Hobbiton movie set is located. 

The entire area around Hobbiton makes you feel like you're in the movies! Hobbiton is surround by green rolling hills dotted with sheep. We were lucky enough to camp only a few minutes away from the movie set. It literally felt like we were camping in the Hobbiton movie set! After staying the night only a couple minutes down the road, we woke up early to take one of the first tours around the Hobbiton movie set. We usually don't pay for tours like thisâ€¦ However, the tour around the Hobbiton movie set was totally worth it!! If you're on the North Island of New Zealand you should definitely take the time to take a tour around Hobbiton! 

If you want to know what it's like to visit Hobbiton New Zealand check out this VLOG!

title: 29 Hours of Travel | Koh Tao to Chiang Mai
description:
âœˆï¸  Check out the travel app we created that helps you find incredibly cheap flights to the amazing destinations all over the world! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160306 â¬…ï¸

Location: Koh Tao (ferry) to Chumpton (bus) to Bangkok (overnight train) to Chiang Mai (FINALLY).

We left the island paradise of Koh Tao to travel overland to the far North of Thailand, Chiang Mai. We took a ferry from Koh Tao to Chumpon. Then we took a bus from Chumpon to Bangkok. After arriving in Bangkok at 9 p.m. we took an overnight night train from Bangkok to Chiang Mai. 

The train ride from Bangkok to Chiang Mai took 14 hours, and unfortunately we got stuck in 3rd class! We didn't book our ticket for the overnight train ahead of time, so we when we arrived in Bangkok they only had 3rd class tickets available. It was impossible to sleep on the overnight train from Bangkok to Chiang Mai! 

By the time we arrive in Chiang Mai, Thailand, we were exhausted. However, we pulled ourselves out of bed and quickly fell in love with city of Chiang Mai! Traveling from Koh Tao to Chiang Mai overland was rough, but it was totally worth it!

Over land travel in Thailand is an experience in and of itself!

title: Bangkok to Hanoi | FIRST PHO IN VIETNAM!
description:
âœˆï¸  We created an app to help you save up to 80% on international flights! Try it risk free  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160328 â¬…ï¸

Location: Bangkok, Thailand to Hanoi, Vietnam. 

Traveling from Bangkok to Hanoi was a treat in comparison to the rough overland travel we'd grown accustom to over the past few weeks. Today we flew from Bangkok (BKK) to Hanoi (HAN) via Veit Jet.

Veit Jet offered the cheapest price between Bangkok and Hanoi. I had read some bad reviews about the airline. However, I have to say that our trip from BKK was HAN was very enjoyable. Checkin at the Bangkok Airport was a breeze, and flight left and arrived on time.

Once we arrived at the Hanoi Airport, things didn't quite a smoothly. Immigration took at least two hours. Then we had trouble finding the public bus into the city center of Hanoi. However, we quickly forgot all of our problems when we were upgrade to a suite room at the Hilton Garden Inn Hanoi!

If you want to know what it's like flying from Bangkok to Hanoi check out this VLOG!

title: BATU CAVES + VALENTINES DAY Q&A
description:
âœˆï¸  We created FareDrop to help you score super cheap international flights! Try it risk free and get flight deals up to 80% off  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160214 â¬…ï¸

Location: Batu Caves, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia

Visiting the Batu Caves was the highlight of our trip to Kuala. If you're planning a trip to Kuala Lumpur Malaysia, you must add the Batu Caves to your itinerary!

The Batu Caves has been transformed into a hindu temple. The mixture of intricate temple decorations, and the sheer scales of the caves make for breathtaking experience.

In order to get inside the caves you need to climb 272 stairs. On the way up the stairs (and in the cave) you'll see tons of monkeys! The monkey can get really aggressive if you bring food.  

If you want to know what it's like to visit the Batu Caves in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia check out this VLOG!

We'd like to say thanks to +Mark Wiens for the inspiring video - A Tour of The Batu Caves Temple in Kuala Lumpur - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GVogESODiIo

title: THE BEST Thai Cooking School | Chiang Mai Thailand
description:
âœˆï¸  Want hidden flight deals to international destinations at up to 80% off? FareDrop is our secret weapon for finding the best deals! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160312 â¬…ï¸

Today's adventure brought to you by: http://www.chiang-mai-cooking-school.com/

You can't visit Chiang Mai, Thailand without taking an authentic Thai cooking class! We had the opportunity to spend a full day at the Thai Secret Cooking School. Obviously we haven't been to every cooking school in Chiang Mai, but I can very confidently say the Thai Secret Cooking School is by far the best cooking school in Chiang Mai! 

The day started with a trip to the local market to pick up ingredients that we would use during our cooking class. After that we took a short drive to the cooking school. The cooking is also an organic farm (and their lovely home!). So before we began our cooking class, we went out to the garden and picked ingredients like flowers and herbs to cook our delicious Thai food!

During the cooking class, we chose to learn to cook pad thai, spring rolls, Penang curry paste,  Penang curry with pork, mango sticky rice, and other Thai dishes. May is the instructor that teaches the Thai cooking class. She has an awesome personality and makes everything so much fun! She definitely makes the experience even greater! 

If you are visiting Chiang Mai, and you love food half as much as we do - Definitely go to a Thai cooking school. The Thai Secret Cooking School comes with our absolute highest recommendations! We had a blast!

Location: Chiang Mai Night Bazaar - Chiang Mai, Thailand
After being in Chiang Mai for a week and checking out both the Saturday Night Market and the Sunday night market, it was time for us the visit the Chiang Mai Night Bazaar.

To be completely honest the Chiang Mai Night Bazaar was a little underwhelming compared to the other markets we had been to in Chiang Mai. However, we were still able to find some fun foods to eat.

The best thing about the night bazaar is that it's open every night. If you aren't in Chiang Mai on the weekend. This will be your only opportunity for visiting a night market.

title: DIVING IN THE RED SEA! Sunken Plane & Military Tank | Aqaba, Jordan
description:
Scuba diving in the Red Sea (in Aqaba, Jordan) is one of the best dives of our lives! We got to dive a sunken C130 plane and a M42 tank both full of fish and coral. Right before we surfaced, we saw a new sea creature for the first time!!! Last night we were freezing in the desert, and today we are scuba diving in the Red Sea! The weather in Jordan keeps surprising us!

Travel vlog 606 | Red Sea, Aqaba, Jordan | Country #87/100 | Filmed February 2019

TODAY WAS AMAZING. But so is every other day in the Galapagos Islands! Today we woke up on the Natural Paradise bright and early and took a boat ride around Punta Vicente Roca. We saw tons of animals in the water, on the rocks, and in the sky. Then we got to jump in and have the best snorkeling of our lives. We saw orca whales, sea lions, sea turtles, penguins, and much more! After a BBQ lunch on the roof, we sailed to an island full of marine iguanas and the cutest baby sea lions on the planet!

title: STINKY TOFU | Taipei Street Food
description:
âœˆï¸  Check out the travel app we created that helps you find incredibly cheap flights to the amazing destinations all over the world! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160212 â¬…ï¸

STINKY TOFU | Taipei's Most Disgusting Street Food...

Location: Taipei, Taiwan

Eating street food in Taipei was the highlight of our trip. Most of the street food that was had was absolutely delicious. However, the STINKY TOFU that we bought from a street was NOT. From the first day we visited Taipei, we could smell the stink from the stinky tofu wafting down the streets. There's not mistaking the pungent smell as it obtrusively enters your nostrils. 

We had debated the entire trip whether or not we were brave enough to try the fermented tofu. On our last day in Taipei, I succeeded in convincing Kara to try stinky tofu with me! There seem to be a lot of locals who enjoy stinky tofu and consider it a local delicacy. However, our American taste buds did not. It tasted just as bad it smells!!!

Kara does an amazing job explaining what like. If you want to see what it's like to try stinky tofu on the streets of Taipei check out this VLOG starting around 8:28!

We'd like to say thanks to Mark Wiens for the inspiring video Stinky Tofu - Eating Smelly Tofu in China! - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ylW94Ff_S0g 

We also have to give thanks to Off the Great Wall and their video that let us know what to expect as Americans - New Yorkers Trying Stinky Tofu For The Very First Time - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xxf5hmDhPLE

Thanks for watching! If you want to follow our adventure, you do so using any of the social media links below!

title: EXPLORING SEOUL'S GRAND PALACE + Korean Fried Chicken!
description:
Planning a trip to Seoul? We want to make sure you have an amazing time! So, we put together a travel guide with 9 things you must do on your first trip to Seoul - http://karaandnate.com/9-things-you-must-do-in-seoul/ 

This ended up being one of our favorite days in Seoul! We squeezed so much into one day. First we visited the Gyeongbokgung Palace. It's massive and you could get lost exploring all day. It's popular to rent traditional dresses and take pictures in front of the detailed buildings which makes it a really fun place to walk around. The changing of the guards is also a super entertaining show to watch! Next we visited the picturesque village of Bukchon Hanok! And finally ended the night eating traditional Korean Fried Chicken at the park where all the local teens pitch tents and hang out all night!

title: Flying from the DR to Mexico on American Airlines | Thoughts on New DFW Centurion Lounge
description:
Thank you for 500k! We're giving away an epic campervan trip and $1,000! Enter the giveaway here https://karaandnate.com/500k-giveaway/
Thank you Karma Campervans for making this possible. If you don't win the giveaway, you can learn more about booking your own trip here https://www.karmacampervans.com/

On our last day in the Dominican Republic, we did something CRAZY that we've never done before. We checked ourselves into an all-inclusive resort and turned off ALL our screens for 24 hours.

As 2018 was coming to an end, we wanted to spend one whole day with no distractions reflecting on our year and making plans for 2019 (& enjoying the resort ;)).

We couldn't BELIEVE how much we accomplished in such a short time away from our phones, computers, cameras, and internet. We even came up with some awesome post-travel vlog ideas!

Our day of bliss came to an abrupt end with a 4:30 a.m. wake up call to fly from the Domincan Republic to Cancun, Mexico. It was a long travel day with stops in Miami and Dallas (both with Centurion Lounges!), and finally Cancun where we got on a bus to take us 3 hours to our final destination of Tulum.

We spent 3 weeks "workationing" in Tulum, so the next vlog will be traveling home Christmas!

Travel vlog 578 | La Romana, Dominican Republic | Country #83/100

title: SECRET POOL Kuang Si Waterfall | Luang Prabang
description:
âœˆï¸  Want hidden flight deals to international destinations at up to 80% off? FareDrop is our secret weapon for finding the best deals! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160321 â¬…ï¸

Mari Johnson's Kuang Si Waterfall Video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MKPhB5q680I

The Kuang Si Waterfalls in Luang Prabang are without a doubt the most beautiful waterfalls we have ever seen! If you're visiting Luang Prabang, Laos, you MUST take a day trip to the Kuang Si Waterfalls.

If you're comfortable on a motorbike, we'd highly recommend renting a motor bike and driving yourself to the waterfalls. It's a very beautiful drive! Once at the Kuang Si Waterfalls you can pay a small fee to park your bike and it will be safe and sound! 

The waterfalls are separated into different levels. The falls get more beautiful with each level you ascend. The final waterfall is a huge 100+ foot waterfall. Most people stop on the bridge below to admire the falls. However, if you hike up the path beside the waterfall, and you're willing to "break the rules", you'll be rewarded with the amazing experience of sitting on the edge of the Kuang Si Falls!

If you want to know what it's like to motor bike to the Kuang Si Waterfall in Luang Prabang check out this VLOG!

title: Shopping for Knock-Offs on PETALING STREET in Chinatown | Kuala Lumpur
description:
âœˆï¸  Want hidden flight deals to international destinations at up to 80% off? FareDrop is our secret weapon for finding the best deals! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160218 â¬…ï¸

Location: Petaling Street, Chinatown, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia

Petaling Street Kuala Lumpur's Chinatown is a treasure trove of knock-off and merchandise! Need a fake pair of Ray-Bans, Nikes, or Rolex? I guarantee you can find what you're looking for in Kuala Lumpur's Chinatown Market.

Even if you don't enjoy shopping this is an experience that shouldn't be missed next time you visit Kuala Lumpur. You'll be entertained by sheer amount stuff in the market, as well as the sales tactics the hawkers use.

I would devote about an hour of time to visiting Chinatown in Kuala Lumpur. You can only look at sunglasses and watches for so long. After you're finished at the market, you can enjoy Kuala Lumpur's best Chinese food at any of the local street vendor stands. 

If you want to know what it's like Kuala Lumpur's Chinatown, check out this VLOG!

title: Bangkok to Koh Tao by BUS and FERRY
description:
âœˆï¸  Want hidden flight deals to international destinations at up to 80% off? FareDrop is our secret weapon for finding the best deals! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160228 â¬…ï¸

Yesterday we travel from Bangkok to Koh Tao by bus and ferry. The entire over land journey between Bangkok and Koh Tao took about 15 hours. We got on the bus in Bangkok around 6 p.m. and we arrived on the island of Koh Tao around 10 a.m. the next morning.

The entire journey cost us around $20 each... If you're looking for the cheapest way to get between Bangkok and Koh Tao, this is probably you best option. However, if you value you time, I would highly recommend flying from Bangkok and then taking the ferry to Koh Tao.

Our journey included several random stops, including a random bus station in the middle of the night, getting dropped off in the middle road, and arriving at the ferry pier at 4 a.m.. It was definitely one of our hardest travel days.

If you want to know what it's like to travel between bangkok and koh tao via bus and ferry, check out this VLOG!

title: AMAZiNG SUNSET | Victoria Peak | Hong Kong
description:
âœˆï¸  Check out the travel app we created that helps you find incredibly cheap flights to the amazing destinations all over the world! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160208 â¬…ï¸

Location: Victoria Peak, Hong Kong

Victoria Peak offers the best views of Hong Kong harbor! If you want to make sure you get the best views of Hong Kong, head to Victoria about a 2 hours before sunset. That will give you time to get up the mountain to enjoy the sunset as well as the neon lights lights of Hong Kong harbor that light up after dark!

There are several ways to get to the top of Victoria Peak. You can hike (up a TON of stairs), you can ride a local bus to the top, or you can take the peak tram. The Peak Tram is the most expensive way to get to the top of the mountain, but it's also the most expensive! We took the local bus to the top of Victoria, and we really enjoyed the views of Hong Kong Island on the way the to the top.

This sunset was actually captured from the Mcdonalds that's inside the mall on top of the Peak, and the views from the Harbor were captured from the Lion's Pavilion. 

If you want to know what it's like to watch the sunset from the top of Victoria Peak in Hong Kong check out this VLOG!

We'd like to say thanks to Yellow Productions for the inspiring video - The Peak Hong Kong Travel Guide - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tSe96h-Wouk

We also have to give thanks to Samuel & Audery and their inspiring video - Peak Tram Ride along with stunning views of Hong Kong Island and Victoria Harbor from The Peak (å¤ªå¹³å±±) - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Py2n_4QyuQo

title: BURMESE BBQ & GOLDEN BUDDHAS | Mandalay, Myanmar
description:

Thank you Paukan Cruises! http://paukan.com/ Our last day of our Irrawaddy River Cruise was a great one! We sadly left the ship after 10 days and visited a pagoda with what Buddhists believe is the holiest Buddha statue in the world - the only one built during his lifetime. Next we got to see how the gold leaves that are placed on the statue are pounded for hours and hours. And lastly we visited the largest book in the world. We ended the day with traditional Burmese Barbecue, and thatâ€™s a wrap on our incredible Myanmar trip!!

title: Luxury Mekong River Cruise | Luang Say Cruises
description:
âœˆï¸  Want hidden flight deals to international destinations at up to 80% off? FareDrop is our secret weapon for finding the best deals! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160316.1 â¬…ï¸

This adventure was made possible by Mekong River Cruises - http://www.luangsay.com/

Cruising down the Mekong River on a luxury riverboat from Huay Xai to Luang Prabang was an amazing experience. This river cruise with Luang Say Cruises easily ranks in my top three experience of the entire trip. The northern Mekong river cruise starts on the Laos border city of Huay Xai. Crossing the border from Chiang Khong to Hauy Xi was extremely easy thanks to Luang Say Cruise's helpful staff that walked us through the entire process! 

We boarded our luxury river boat around 9 a.m., and by 9:30 we were cruising down the Mekong River. After cruising down the river for a couple of hours, we were severed an amazing lunch buffet. After lunch we continued down stream until we got to a small village on the bank of the Mekong River. Our boat docked on the shore while we explored the village to learn how the local mountain people live.

After visiting the village our luxury cruise continued down river until we arrived at the Luang Say Lodge. We spent the night in a beautiful bungalow that offered amazing views of the Mekong River. That night we were served an amazing dinner, and the next morning we woke up to awesome views of the misty Mekong River.

If you want to know what it's like to go on a luxury cruise down the Mekong River check out this VLOG!

Thanks for watching! If you want to follow our adventure, you do so using any of the social media links below!

title: Bua Thong Waterfalls | Chiang Mai's Sticky Waterfalls
description:
âœˆï¸  Check out the travel app we created that helps you find incredibly cheap flights to the amazing destinations all over the world! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160313 â¬…ï¸

Location: Bua Thong Waterfalls (Sticky Waterfalls) - Chiang Mai, Thailand

We rented motor bikes and took about a two hour drive out of the city to some really cool waterfalls! They are called the Bua Thong 
Waterfalls aka â€œSticky Waterfalls.â€ They get their name because of mineral in the water allows you to walk on the rocks without falling!

Driving to the Bua Thong Waterfalls is quite the haul. It us over two hours to get there. However, I do think the drive is worth it. You literally feel like spiderman climbing up the sticky waterfalls.

It's such a weird feeling for a waterfall to be "sticky" it messes with your mind because you think you're going to slip, but you can just climb right up the waterfall. As far as I know, the Bua Thong waterfalls are the only waterfalls in the world that have this sticky feature.

If you want to know what it's like to visit the Sticky Waterfalls in Chiang Mai, Thailand check out this VLOG!

Thanks for watching! If you want to follow our adventure, you do so using any of the social media links below!

Location: DoubleTree - Kuala Lumpur Malaysia

Staying at the DoubleTree in Kuala Lumpur Malaysia is a fantastic experience, IF YOU'RE A HILTON GOLD MEMBER! As a gold member you get access to the executive lounge as well as free breakfast! 

The views of Kuala Lumpur from the executive lounge are amazing! The lounge offers great views of the Peteronas Towers as well as great views of the surround mountains. We could help but take some time lapses of the amazing views! 

If you're traveling to Southeast Asia as a Hilton gold member, you shouldn't miss your chance to stay at the DoubleTree. By enjoying lunch in the Makana Kitchen and lunch and dinner in the executive lounge, you can save a ton of money! Especially if you're staying with points ;)

title: Exploring the Luang Prabang Night Market
description:
âœˆï¸  Check out the travel app we created that helps you find incredibly cheap flights to the amazing destinations all over the world! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160318 â¬…ï¸

Location: Luang Prabang Night Market

The Luang Prabang Night Market is one of the most unique night markets in Southeast Asia. The night market is completely covered in in red and blue tents. The market is beautiful from above. As the sunsets the lights begin to come on, and the night market takes on a magical glow. 

The Luang Prabang Night Market sells all kinds of local goods. Unlike other Southeast Asian countries. The market isn't filled with knock off goods. I didn't see a single pair of RayBans for sale. Instead the vendors were selling hand made jewelry and rice whisky with scorpions! 

In comparison to other Southeast Asian countries, the night market is much smaller and the vendors are much less pushy. You could walk through the night market in about an hour, and only get hounded to buy things a couple of times.

If you want to know what it's like to visit the Luang Prabang Night Market check out this VLOG!

Thanks for watching! If you want to follow our adventure, you do so using any of the social media links below!

title: Koh Tao, Thailand TERRIFYING NIGHT DIVING| PADI Certification at Sairee Cottage
description:
âœˆï¸  We created an app to help you save up to 80% on international flights! Try it risk free  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160303 â¬…ï¸

Location: Koh Tao, Thailand

Diving in Koh Tao is the most popular activity on the island. It seems like everything in Koh Tao revolves around scuba diving. We had originally planned to just do a few fun dives during our week in Koh Tao. However, we were quickly talked in to getting our Advanced Open Water certification! 

Koh Tao is one of the cheapest places in the world to get diving certifications! Our advanced diving certification cost approximately $250 USD. We had an amazing experience diving in Koh Tao and we would highly recommend to anyone!

The only draw back to the diving was that the visibility was pretty poor. We had heard great things about the visibility around Koh Tao, but we went during low season so the water around the island wasn't as clear.

If you want to know what it's like diving in Koh Tao check out this VLOG!

title: Koh Tao Thailand | A DAY IN PARADISE!
description:
âœˆï¸  We created FareDrop to help you score super cheap international flights! Try it risk free and get flight deals up to 80% off  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160305 â¬…ï¸

Location: Koh Tao, Thailand. 

Koh Tao Thailand is a diving paradise that shouldn't be missed if you're visiting Southern Thailand! The island of Koh Tao is one of the cheapest places in Thailand and the world get your diving certification. However, there way more to do on Koh Tao than just diving.

In today's vlog we rented motor bikes to explore the south side of the island, and we snorkeled off the coast of Freedom Beach and Shark Bay. Plus, if night life is your thing, the island of Koh Tao has some of the best night life in all of Thailand. The area around Sairee Beach is the place to go if you want night life! 

If you want to know what it's like to spend a day exploring Koh Tao Thailand, check out this VLOG!

Today our alarms went off WAY earlier than usual! We got up before the sun rise and headed back into the Dubai Desert where we went on our first HOT AIR BALLOON RIDE! It totally exceeded our expectations. We got to watch the sun rise over the dunes and even saw oryxes and camels trotting through the desert. It was magical! Once we landed we went back to the same Desert Camp as the night before for a delicious breakfast! We are continually impressed with the food quality in the middle of the desert ;) We were back at our hotel super early, so we rested and caught up on work before heading downtown for what every tourist must see - the tallest building in the world (Burj Khalifa) and the light show, but unfortunately they were both cancelled. That just gives us a reason to come back one day! :)

title: Chiang Mai to Chiang Khong by BUS
description:
âœˆï¸  We created an app to help you save up to 80% on international flights! Try it risk free  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160315 â¬…ï¸

Location: Chiang Mai, Chiang Rai, and Chiang Khong, Thailand

Today we embarked on an overland journey from Chiang Mai to Chiang Khong. First we took a bus from Chiang Mai to Chiang Rai. This journey took about three and half hours. We left from the Chiang Mai bus terminal at 11:30 via the green bus company.

After arriving in Chiang Rai we quickly boarded a local bus that would take us the rest of the way to Chiang Khong. The local bus from Chiang Rai to Chiang Khong took about two hours, and there was no A/C on the bus. It was a hot ride, but also a very beautiful ride because we got to see the rural country side of Thailand.

After arriving in Chiang Khong, we caught a tuk tuk to our guest house. The journey from Chiang Mai to Chiang Khong was more pleasant than expected. Anytime we have to ride on buses all day, I always prepare myself for the worst. However, I would recommend going overland between these two cities to anyone.

If you want to know what it's like getting from Chiang Mai to Chiang Khong via bus check out this VLOG!

Vlog 41 of many. 
Location: Angkor Wat, Siem Reap, Cambodia. 

Our first day of exploring the temples of Angkor was AWESOME! Today we explored the "big loop". This included the temples of East Mabon, Ta Som, Neak Pean, and Preah Khan.

I think we managed to shoot this entire VLOG without a single person in one of our temple shots. We visited the main temples of Angkor Wat the next day, but we actually enjoyed the "big loop" more because we able to avoid the crowds.

When visit the big loop at Angkor, make sure to arrive early and you will have the temples to yourself!

title: UGLY TRUTH Luang Prabang Alms Ceremony
description:
âœˆï¸  We created an app to help you save up to 80% on international flights! Try it risk free  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160319 â¬…ï¸

Location: Luang Prabang, Loas 

The alms ceremony is a beautiful tradition that has been spoiled by tourists. Everyone jostles to get the best picture of the monks. As one person moves in closer, so do the rest. The next thing you know, people are standing two feet away from the monks during the alms ceremony.

I believe at one point in the time, the alm ceremony in Luang Prabang was a beautiful ceremony, but sadly it's now turned into more of a tourist spectacle. 

Even though we've been extremely negative of the giving of the alms ceremony up until this point, I do believe it's worth the trip. If you're going to be in Luang Prabang, don't skip the alms ceremony. However, mentally prepare yourself ahead of time for the rude tourists you encounter. I believe that you can go to the alms ceremony without contributing to the problem. Just stay on the opposite side of the street and sit respectfully as the monks walk by. The rude tourist are going to show up anyway. You might as well at least get a glimpse of the monks collecting their alms.

If you want to know what it's really like to go to the Luang Prabang Alms Ceremony, check out this VLOG!

Thanks for watching! If you want to follow our adventure, you can do so using any of the social media links below!

title: The REAL Thai Lantern Festival | Authentic Loy Krathong in Chiang Mai, Thailand (Part 1)
description:
Everyone has seen the beautiful Lantern Festival (Yee Peng) celebrated in Chiang Mai, but little know the fact that it is actually a Chinese festival. On the same night, the Thai festival of Loy Krathong is celebrated, so we decided to celebrate the local way. We made Krathongs with kids at a school where our friend Paddy works to release in the river, but first we stumbled upon the most beautiful monk ceremony we've ever seen!

 ğŸŒ We created Daily Drop Pro to help you score super cheap travel with cash or points! Try it risk free and get flight deals up to 80% off â¡ï¸ 
https://www.dailydrop.com/pro?utm_source=karaandnate&utm_medium=youtube&utm_campaign=yt%20karaandnate

This day consisted of the Kiwi tradition called "Tim Tam Slam" which started our day off just right. First you start with a Tim Tam which is a traditional New Zealand Biscuit. They're amazing to begin with but even more amazing when you combine them with coffee in act known as the Tim Tam Slam.

The Tim Tam Slam starts by biting off opposing ends of the the Tim Tam. Then you insert one of the Tim Tam into the coffee and you suck the coffee through the other end of the Tim Tam. As soon as the coffee hits your tongue you slam Tim Tam into your mouth! Let's just say it's magical!

Then we went to the powerful Huka Falls, and then to our new campground in Rotorua. We give a tour of our camper and then explore some of the geothermal activity in the area!

If you want to see how to properly do a Tim Tam Slam check out this VLOG!

title: Mekong River Cruise | DAY 2
description:
âœˆï¸  We created FareDrop to help you score super cheap international flights! Try it risk free and get flight deals up to 80% off  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160316 â¬…ï¸

This adventure was made possible by Mekong River Cruises - http://www.luangsay.com/

See day one of our Mekong River cruise here - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yjGa9v4zgdg

Cruising down the Mekong River on a luxury riverboat from Huay Xai to Luang Prabang is an amazing experience. This river cruise with Luang Say Cruises easily ranks in my top three experiences of the entire trip. The northern Mekong river cruise starts on the Laos border city of Huay Xai. Crossing the border from Chiang Khong to Hauy Xi was extremely easy thanks to Luang Say Cruise's helpful staff that walked us through the entire process! 

Day 2 of our luxury river cruise down the Mekong River cruise started at the Luang Say Lodge. Early in the morning I opened the windows of my bungalow to reveal a foggy, but beautiful view of the Mekong River. Next, we had a delicious breakfast. Then, we board our luxury river boat to continue cruising down the Mekong River.

A couples hours into our journey down stream we stopped a local village to see how they made silk scarves and rice whiskey. After visiting the village we were served a delicious lunch on the boat. After lunch we stopped at a really neat cave on the side of the river. The cave was covered in buddha statues.

If you want to know what it's like to go on a luxury cruise down the Mekong River check out this VLOG!

Thanks for watching! If you want to follow our adventure, you do so using any of the social media links below!

title: Doi Suthep + Coffee Plantation | Chiang Mai Day Trip
description:
âœˆï¸  We created FareDrop to help you score super cheap international flights! Try it risk free and get flight deals up to 80% off  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160309 â¬…ï¸

Vlog 58 of many. 
Location: Doi Suthep, Chiang Mai, Thailand. 

We rented motor bikes and drove to the most beautiful temple in Chiang Mai - Doi Suthep! Doi Suthep is set up on top of a mountain. It's an easy 30 minute motorbike ride outside of the city. We highly recommend renting a motor bike to drive to the Doi Suthep Temple because the roads are really curvy and a lot of fun on a bike.

Do Suthep is a great day trip, especially if you continue on to the mountain village and coffee plantation. If you want to visit all three in the same day, it will take 6 - 8 hours. However, I believe this is one of the best day trips in Chiang Mai! 

Chiang Mai is an amazing city, but a day trip outside of the city will give you an even greater appreciation for the city. Chiang Mai is quickly becoming our favorite city in Thailand! Next up, a day trip to the sticky waterfall!

title: Luang Prabang to Vientiane to Bangkok
description:
âœˆï¸  Check out the travel app we created that helps you find incredibly cheap flights to the amazing destinations all over the world! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160324 â¬…ï¸

Going overland from Luang Prabang to Vientiane then to Bangkok is an EXHAUSTING journey! Thankful we survived the back to back overnight bus and train combo. We started in Luang Prabang. There we boarded a "VIP" sleeper bus to Vientiane. The ride to Vientiane took about 10 hours. However, it was a rough 10 hours. The roads between Luang Prabang and Vientiane are winding mountain roads. We slide back an forth in our seats the entire time.

We arrived in Vientiane around 5 a.m.. We were dropped off at a bus station a little ways outside of the city. We caught a "taxi" into the city and wasted the day at a coffee shop. We were picked up at 3 p.m. for our overnight train between Vientiane and Bangkok.

The overnight train from Vientiane to Bangkok took a total 14 hours. The ride wasn't bad at all! Make sure you at least book the second class sleeper car. I wouldn't suggest that my worst enemy ride the bus from Luang Prabang to Vientiane. However, I wouldn't hesitate to recommend the overnight from Vientiane to Bangkok to a friend!

If you want to know what it's like traveling overland from Luang Prabang to Bangkok check out this VLOG!

title: TAJ MAHAL OF MYANMAR! Irrawaddy River Cruise Days 8 & 9
description:

Thank you Paukan Cruises! http://paukan.com/ Days 8 and 9 of our Irrawaddy River Cruise through Myanmar were jam packed! title: BEST Bangkok Rooftop Bar
description:
âœˆï¸  We created an app to help you save up to 80% on international flights! Try it risk free  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160324.1 â¬…ï¸

Searching from the Best Bangkok Rooftop Bar? Look no further than the Octave Rooftop Bar on top of the Marriot hotel in Bangkok. Obviously, Kara and I haven't been to every Rooftop bar in Bangkok, so we can't say for sure that the Octave Rooftop Lounge & Bar is the best. However, we can highly recommend it!

I had done a ton of research about which rooftop bar to visit in Bangkok. I was originally inspired by the Hangover movie, which I'm sure most are familiar with. I had originally wanted to go to the rooftop bar where the Hangover was filmed. However, I learned that it's crazy expensive and over-crowded. That seemed to be the problem with many of the roof top bars in the city. 

The Octave roof top bar was perfect. It offered amazing views of the city of Bangkok, it wasn't over crowded, and the drinks were a reasonable price.

Thanks for watching! If you want to follow our adventure, you do so using any of the social media links below!

title: SECRET TOUR OF THE KGB HOUSE | Riga Latvia
description:
Riga, Latvia has become one of our favorite places this summer! We took a tour of the KGB House which has been turned into a museum. However after our tour, our guide took us to the untouched basement and upstairs of the house, and it was very spooky. This vlog also includes a local Latvian lunch of dumplings which we were charged by the weight, and a massive cup of coffee. Both SUPER affordable compared to what we've been paying in Iceland!

title: Kayaking + Snorkeling | Koh Tao, Thailand
description:
âœˆï¸  Check out the travel app we created that helps you find incredibly cheap flights to the amazing destinations all over the world! Try it risk free â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160302 â¬…ï¸

Location: Oslob, Cebu Philippines

Need a break from diving in Koh Tao? A day of snorkeling and kayaking in Koh Tao can be the perfect adventure! We rented a two snorkels and a two person kayak for only $15.

We spent the afternoon kayaking to some of the best snorkeling spots within paddling distant of Sairee beach. The waves ended up getting pretty big, which made kayaking much harder.

The visibility while we were snorkeling was actually better than it was on any of our dives. We saw a ton of fish. Koh Tao is definitely one of the best places we've ever snorkeled! 

If you want to know what it's like kayaking and snorkeling around Koh Tao, check out this VLOG!

title: Luang Prabang AUTHENTIC Alms + Nate's Birthday!
description:
âœˆï¸  We created FareDrop to help you score super cheap international flights! Try it risk free and get flight deals up to 80% off  â¡ï¸  https://faredrop.app/ytd_160322 â¬…ï¸

Location: Luang Prabang, Loas 

The Luang Prabang alms ceremony is one of the top tourist attractions in Laos. Unfortunately, the amount of rude tourists that attend the alms ceremony can completely ruin the experience. After a frustrating experience a couple days ago, Nate woke up early again in search of Luang Prabang's authentic alms ceremony. 

Getting away from the main street completely transformed the experience! The alms ceremony on the main road feels more like a monk parade for the tourist. However, if you visit some of the side streets of Luang Prabang, you can still find some locals participating in the alms ceremony, and you'll avoid the hoards of tourists!

If you want to know what it's like to see an authentic Luang Prabang Alms Ceremony, check out this VLOG!

The biggest tourist attraction in Rotorua New Zealand is the natural hot springs. However, a lot of the hot springs in New Zealand cost $30 to visit. We didnâ€™t exactly want to pay $30 to watch water boil so we explored two free hot springs options in Rotorua New Zealand.

First we dug our own natural hot spring on the shore of lake Rotorua. Digging your own natural hot spring is one of those things that sounds way better than it is in real life. Youâ€™ll just have to watch the video to see!

Next we visited free local park with tons of natural hot springs and geothermal activity. That was plenty for us, but if you want see a geyser unfortunately youâ€™ll have to pay to visit Hellâ€™s Gate or one of the paid geothermal parks in Rotorua New Zealand.

title: Mating Giant Tortoises & 25 Day Old Baby! Galapagos Islands Cruise Day 4
description:
THIS ADVENTURE MADE POSSIBLE BY: http://bit.ly/royalgalapagos

Today in the amazing Galapagos islands, we hiked up to the second largest active volcano crater in the world! Then we visited a turtle breeding center where we saw everything from tiny baby tortoises and mating mom and dads! On this island of Isabella, too many introduced animals have endangered this species of tortoises by eating the eggs and babies. Thanks to this breeding center, they are being raised until they are 5 years old and then released throughout the Galapagos Islands to mate naturally. It was another great day aboard the Natural Paradise :)

Today we celebrated Carnaval in La Paz, Bolivia, which we learned meant dressing up and running around and spraying people with foam. Here's the official definition according to Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia:

The Carnival of Oruro is a religious festival dating back more than 200 years that takes place in Oruro, Bolivia. It is one of UNESCO's Masterpieces of the Oral and Intangible Heritage of Humanity. Originally an indigenous festival, the celebration later was transformed to incorporate a Christian ritual around the Virgin of Candelaria (Virgin of SocavÃ³n), which takes place on March 2. The traditional Llama llama or Diablada became the leading traditional dance of the festival. Throughout the festival, more than 48 groups of folk dancers specializing in 18 different folk dances perform a pilgrimage to the Shrine of the Tunnel every Saturday of the carnival in a traditional parade.

title: SEA LIONS EVERYWHERE. BEST DAY EVER. Galapagos Cruise Day 6
description:
THIS ADVENTURE MADE POSSIBLE BY: http://bit.ly/royalgalapagos
Skip to 5:40 through the end for the best part of the whole trip!

Two of our favorite parts of the Galapagos Islands cruise happened today! Champion Island is loaded with adorable sea lions, and we got to swim with hundreds of them! Then on Floreana Island, we got to witness the beautiful blue-footed booby male do his mating dance ritual! We also got to visit the first ever mailbox in the Galapagos on Post Office Island which is still being used like they traditionally did in the 1800s!

How Do I Enter?
Use the form on the site to submit your name and email. That's it! If you like, you can complete the extra actions for more entries into the giveaway.

March 5th, 2018 at 11:59 PST

How Will You Choose The Winner?
We're using Gleam.io to host this giveaway. Their software allows us to randomly select a winner from all of the entries.

How Will You Announce The Winner?
We will announce the winner via email.

Is This Giveaway Open World Wide?
Yes!

What's Included?

International airport transfers (pick-up and drop-off) in Kathmandu by private vehicle
Hotel accommodations with breakfast in Kathmandu/Bhaktapur
Entrance fee and private tour of Bhaktapur UNESCO World Heritage district
Nepali Welcome Dinner
Teahouse accommodations with hot showers during trek
Flights to/from Lukla, including airport tax and transfers
Licensed, English-speaking guide
Porter for carrying all luggage on trek (up to 30 kg between two people)
Trek staff gear and insurance
All local tariffs for the services provided
Trek map (to keep)
Trekking permits
Down jackets, sleeping bags, trail map, first-aid supplies, and filter water bottles to use during trek
What's not included?

Nepal entry visas ($40 for up to 30 days)
Food and drinks while trekking
International travel and medical rescue insurance
International flights
